reviews.review_text:
Setlist Update & Whole Show? Thanx SIRMick.  I am so happy to have this show despite the sound quality.  It might hurt some of your little ears.  The highlight for me was Hard To Handle.  This is a sloppy joe show.  The band sounds either tired, transitioning from 2 drummers, or both.  Even the short exploratory part of The Other One sounds a bit logey.  I do love the Pig shows and enjoyed hearing this.
I checked DeadBase 10, The Taper's Copendium, and Setlist.com and I believe this to be the entire show, cuts notwithstanding.  If you allow for Beat It On Down being the last tune of the 1st set (unfortunately Bob's statement of set break is omitted)and out of order, the complete show fits nicely on the necessary 2 discs as:
Disc 1
Bertha
Sugar Magnolia
King Bee
Casey Jones
Hard to Handle
Greatest Story>
JB Goode
BIODTL
Disc 2
Next Time You See Me
Loser
Truckin'>
Drums>
Other One
Playing
NFA>
GDTRFB>
NFA
Uncle John's (encore)
This just takes a bit of track readjustment.  Peace
